                        <condition key="deficient">The Ms. was probably resewn; the sewing is damaged.&#xD;
The front board is broken and repaired. &#xD;
Traces of leather are visible on the inner side of the front board; traces of leather or discoloration are visible also on <locus target="4v">4v</locus> and 123v. &#xD;
The attachment of the front board has been repaired with synthetic threads.&#xD;
Quire XI is misplaced, its original position must have been between quires IX and X according to the text.&#xD;
Many fols. are affected by humidity.&#xD;
Holes or tears amended on fols. 8, 43, 51.</condition>
