                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#107rb">f. 107rb</locus>
                           <desc>: Donation note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note states that the Ms. was purchased and donated to the church by ʾabuna Gabra Mikāʾel. It mentions also his family members: his father ʾabuna<note> Walda Śǝllāse, mother ʿUṣǝftä Dǝngǝl, wife Walatta Ḥǝywat, son Walda Mikāʾel and his sisters Ḫayla Mikāʾel, Walatta Mikāʾel, Walatta Kidān.
                        </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#113vb">f. 113vb</locus>
                           <desc>: Commemorative notice for the 12th of Maskaram and ʾarke-hymn.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note>
                           The omitted commemorative notice and hymn are written in smaller, compressed script.
                        </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#121vb">f. 121vb</locus>
                           <desc>: Donation note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note>
                           The note has been washed out, but the names of ʾArkä Sǝllus and his wife Walatta Māryām can still be read.
                        </note>
                        </item>
